---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Projects - Jay Lee"
  description="Public-safe AI adoption projects by Jay Lee, including AI Workflow Audit Kit and human-agent operations prototypes."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Projects</p>
        <h1>Artifacts that make the thinking inspectable.</h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        The project page is the bridge between GitHub evidence and the operating story. Public work uses synthetic data only
        and avoids employer or customer material.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>AI Workflow Audit Kit</h3>
        <p>
          A public-safe enterprise AI adoption framework for mapping workflows, selecting AI pilot candidates, defining
          eval gates, and setting responsible capture boundaries.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">20/20 evals</span>
          <span class="tag">6/6 RAG evals</span>
          <span class="tag">synthetic data</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jayjoolee/ai-workflow-audit-kit">Open GitHub repository</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Responsible Skill Capture</h3>
        <p>
          A boundary pattern for capturing approved process knowledge without turning private employee traces, tone, or
          identity into the product.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">governance</span>
          <span class="tag">human accountability</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jayjoolee/ai-workflow-audit-kit/blob/main/docs/responsible-skill-capture.md">Read the protocol</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Loop Lab</h3>
        <p>
          A goal-oriented loop runner prototype for collect, draft, evaluate, and revise workflows. Publication remains
          separate from employer-derived context.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">workflow tooling</span>
          <span class="tag">coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/writing/">Follow build notes</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Open-source tools</p>
        <h2>Small tools, built in the open.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Side of the workbench where adoption thinking meets working code: local-first, privacy-respecting utilities anyone
        can run and inspect.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>photo-trip-timeline</h3>
        <p>
          Auto-detects trips from your Apple Photos and generates a shareable Markdown travel timeline. Place names only —
          your GPS coordinates never leave your Mac.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">local-first</span>
          <span class="tag">privacy</span>
          <span class="tag">Python CLI</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jayjoolee/photo-trip-timeline">Open GitHub repository</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>claude-voice-memo</h3>
        <p>
          Turns any voice recording into a clean speaker-aware transcript plus a key briefing — fully local and private,
          using Claude Code and on-device Whisper.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">on-device STT</span>
          <span class="tag">Claude Code</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jayjoolee/claude-voice-memo">Open GitHub repository</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>dopamind</h3>
        <p>
          An ADHD-friendly learning tool that breaks long-form content into focused, digestible chunks with hooks, key
          points, and a catch-me-up mode. Bring your own API key.
        </p>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag">learning</span>
          <span class="tag">BYOK</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jayjoolee/dopamind">Open GitHub repository</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <figure class="evidence-panel">
      <img src="/assets/report-preview.svg" alt="Sample output preview from the AI Workflow Audit Kit" />
      <figcaption class="panel-caption">
        A portfolio project should show the output shape, not only the repository name.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
